faring under
the plan.

41:32.623 --> 41:36.160 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAMERON BARROWS: Even though we
have a finite
number of species that we're
trying to protect

41:36.194 --> 41:41.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
here, we're really trying to
protect the entire
ecosystem. We're measuring
everything. We

41:41.065 --> 41:46.304 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
want to make sure that this is
an intact system.
We don't want to be able to say
in 75 years,

41:46.337 --> 41:50.575 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you know, we forgot about that
mouse, and
it went extinct. Oh, well.

41:50.608 --> 41:55.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAT WISE: Barrows was on the
scientific advisory
committee that provided guidance
about which

41:55.913 --> 42:00.952 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
areas of the valley need to be
protected,
an effort he says that charted
new ground

42:00.985 --> 42:02.653 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in conservation science.

42:02.687 --> 42:07.658 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAMERON BARROWS: We're striking
this balance
between habitat and development.
And this

42:07.692 --> 42:12.196 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was one of the first places in
the nation
that tried to really strike an
effective balance.

42:12.230 --> 42:15.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, to do that, we had to apply
the best
science we possibly could.

42:16.000 --> 42:21.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Nature is complex. It's really
complex. And
to be able to say this patch is
enough or

42:21.572 --> 42:27.211 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this level of connection is
enough is really
challenging to do that.

42:27.245 --> 42:33.651 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAT WISE: This underpass behind
me plays an
important role in the habitat
plan. It allows

42:33.684 --> 42:39.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
